The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Tech firms ink twin deals
                                                                                                                           6                                                                                      Tech firms ink twin deals
          A STAFF REPORTER                              
	Calcutta, May 5: Domestic IT companies are taking the partnership route to expand their global footprint.         
	Wipro Technologies, the global information technology services division of Wipro Ltd, has agreed to partner US-based Pegasystems to offer business process management solutions to their clients.         
	Wipros local peer HCL Technologies has entered into an alliance with Stellar Asia Pacific to offer business services to new and existing clients in Australia.        
	Wipro and Pegasystems will leverage on each others offerings to deliver faster solutions to clients.         
	The alliance will focus on developing business solutions across a varied range of industry verticals. These solutions will help clients improve customer retention and achieve productivity improvements of 30-40 per cent.         
	We are glad to take our relationship to the next level. Wipro has always been focused on delivering innovative and cost-effective solutions to customers, K.R. Sanjiv, senior vice-president (BTS), Wipro Technologies, said.        
	HCL Technologies alliance with Stellar Asia Pacific focuses on offering business services to new and existing clients in Australia.        
	Stellar provides call centre services and business process outsourcing globally.        
	HCL and Stellar will jointly offer business and outsourcing services to clients by leveraging HCLs back office and technology product capabilities with Stellars customer relationship management skills.         
	Both the firms will target specific industry segments such as banking and financial services, telecom, manufacturing, utilities services, retail and media.                                                                                                                                       
